@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{MS "Introduction"}

GuideCheck is an useful tool for guide creators.@{par}

GuideCheck is checking the whole guide file. A detailed report on any error allows to fix these bugs
very easy.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

 @{MS "Systemrequirements"}

OS2.0 or higher.@{par}

If you are using OS2.1 or higher, then GuideCheck will use the locale.library. The whole output will
appear multilingual.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Featurelist"

 @{MS "Features"}

  ° Very small and fast@{par}

  ° Supports more than 50 guide commands@{par}

  ° Checking links and other references@{par}

  ° AmigaGuide files may be linked together@{par}

  ° Dupe node detection@{par}

  ° Unreferenced node detection@{par}

  ° Illegal character detection within node definitions@{par}

  ° Fully localized@{par}

@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

 @{MS "Distribution"}

This program should be published on every public medium, as long as all files in the archive are
unchanged. If this medium is a CD I expect a free copy. (AminetCDs excluded)@{par}

@{b}GuideCheck is Mailware.@{ub}@{par}

I expect from everybody, who uses GuideCheck regularly, to send me an EMail or post card. I think
this does not hurt anybody, and I will have more fun integrating new features or writing other
tools.@{par}

Updates may be requested from @{b}http://www.geit.de@{ub} and @{b}Aminet@{ub}.@{par}

@{b}I am not liable for injuries or data loss caused by GuideCheck. The use of GuideCheck is your
own responsibility !!!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "HowToInstall" "How to Install GuideCheck"

 @{MS "How to Install GuideCheck"}

Just copy the "GuideCheck" command into the "C:" drawer.@{par}

If you want to use your language, it is required to install the specific catalog file of or country.
English is default and there is no need for a catalog file.@{par}

Thats all!@{par}

@endnode
@node "GuideCheck" "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "GuideCheck"}

GuideCheck is a CLI/Shell only program. The following template is used:@{par}

@{"Name" link "PT_Name"}/A,@{"NoDeepScan" link "PT_NoDeepScan"}/S=@{"NDS" link "PT_NoDeepScan"},@{"NoOther" link "PT_NoOther"}/S=@{"NO" link "PT_NoOther"},@{"NoNodes" link "PT_NoNodes"}/S=@{"NN" link "PT_NoNodes"},@{"NoLinks" link "PT_NoLinks"}/S=@{"NL" link "PT_NoLinks"},@{"NodeNameCheck" link "PT_NodeNameCheck"}/S=@{"NNC" link "PT_NodeNameCheck"},@{"HTDS" link "PT_HTDS"}/S=@{"HT" link "PT_HTDS"},@{"DEBUG" link "PT_DEBUG"}/S@{par}

@endnode
@node "History" "History"

 @{MS "History"}

 @{MC "1.00"}

First official version

 @{MC "1.01"}

BUGFIX: Fixed a bug that causes local commands to report a "Missing Quotation Mark" when containing
a "}".

 @{MC "1.02 - 1.10"}

FEATURE: Now Guidecheck supports @{"multi guide files" link "PT_NoDeepScan"}.@{par}
CHANGED: Many small internal enhancements.

 @{MC "1.11"}

French doc files added! (Thanks to Frédéric Delacroix)

 @{MC "1.12"}

FEATURE: Forgot to implement the \@{FONT} command. (reported by Ronald Schmiers)@{par}
BUGFIX: The \@{BG} and \@{BPEN} commands were creating error messages even if the command was
correct. (reported by Ronald Schmiers)@{par}
BUGFIX: Non existing external guide files caused GuideCheck to quit immediately. This is now fixed.
(reported by Ronald Schmiers)@{par}

 @{MC "1.13"}

BUGFIX: The syntax checker is specifying the exact command that caused an error by viewing its
name.@{par}
BUGFIX: Fixed the \@{SETTABS} command.

 @{MC "1.14"}

FEATURE: Now \@{macro} support.

 @{MC "1.15"}

BUGFIX: Macros without arguments are no longer creating errors.@{par}
FEATURE: Now its possible to abort the syntax output.@{par}
BUGFIX: Macros within Macros are no longer allowed when using guide mode.

 @{MC "1.16"}

FEATURE: New italian catalog and manual. (Thanks to Walter Cazzola)@{par}
FEATURE: New FAQ Chapter included: @{"FileLink" link "FAQSFLINK"}

 @{MC "1.17"}

FEATURE: GuideCheck.rexx included! This script allows to use GuideCheck direct on your Workbench.
(Thanks to Nils Goers)

 @{MC "1.18"}

BUGFIX: Fixed the picture/datatype link problem!

 @{MC "1.19"}

FEATURE: The complete checking of node names is now @{"optional" link "PT_NodeNameCheck"}. The only
chars that are never allowed are: ":" and "/" because these chars indicate a dos path.

 @{MC "1.20 = 1.19"}

Added spanish manual and catalogs (Thanks to Victor M. Gutiérrez)

 @{MC "1.21"}

FEATURE: Added new style checking. (e.g. \@{b} missing)@{par}
FEATURE: \@database must be present at line 1! If not, its handled like a standard text file.@{par}
FEATURE: The color description text of the \@FG and \@BG commands is now entirely checked.@{par}
FEATURE: @{"DEBUG" link "PT_Debug"} option allows to output all linked non guide files.@{par}
FEATURE: New file typ output. (guide, text, binary)

 @{MC "1.22"}

BUGFIX: Some minor corrections.

 @{MC "1.23"}

BUGFIX: Fixed little bug to make it MorphOS compatible.
CHANGED: Updated the manual and the entire archive.@{par}

@endnode
