@node "PT_Name" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: Name"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "Name"}

This argument specifies the name of the guide file.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_NoDeepScan" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: NoDeepScan"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "NoDeepScan"}

Under normal circumstances GuideCheck is scanning all files attached to one guide. So if a link
specifies a node within an other AmigaGuide file than this file will be also checked.@{par}

This option forces GuideCheck to check only the @{"specified" link "PT_Name"} file. Links to other
files will be ignored.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_NoOther" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: NoOther"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "NoOther"}

This switch deactivates the checking of nodes and links. Only the syntax of the guide file is
checked.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_NoNodes" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: NoNodes"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "NoNodes"}

This argument disables the node checking. So GuideCheck is not reporting nodes which are not
referenced in the guide.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_NoLinks" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: NoLinks"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "NoLinks"}

This switch disables the \@LINK check.@{par}

Under normal circumstances GuideCheck is checking the node specified by \@Link, \@TOC, \@Next,
\@Prev oder \@Index commands.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_NodeNameCheck" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: NodeNameCheck"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "NodeNameCheck"}

This switch enables the hard node name checking. Instead of checking for the illegal characters ":"
and "/" this mode activates other characters that should not be used within node names.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_HTDS" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: HTDS"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "HTDS"}

This switch allows to check HTDS-files. HTDS is a datatype system that enhances the original
AmigaGuide command set.@{par}

Currently only some @{"Commands" link "Commands"} are supported and a special @{"macro handling" link "CMD_LMacro"} is used.@{par}

@endnode
@node "PT_DEBUG" "The Pattern of GuideCheck: Debug"
@toc "GuideCheck"

 @{MS "Debug"}

This switch allows to output all linked files. This is useful for larger compilations with images
and sounds.@{par}

@endnode

